quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  7,85,"And to the people of Midian We sent their brother Shu’aib. He said, “O my people! Worship God—you have no other god except Him. A clear proof has already come to you from your Lord. So give just measure and weight, do not defraud people of their property, nor spread corruption in the land after it has been set in order. This is for your own good, if you are ˹truly˺ believers"
  7,86,"And do not lie in ambush on every road—threatening and hindering those who believe in God from His Path and striving to make it ˹appear˺ crooked. Remember when you were few, then He increased you in number. And consider the fate of the corruptors"
  7,87,"If some of you do believe in what I have been sent with while others do not, then be patient until God judges between us. He is the Best of Judges.”"
  7,88,"The arrogant chiefs of his people threatened, “O Shu’aib! We will certainly expel you and your fellow believers from our land, unless you return to our faith.” He replied, “Even if we hate it"
  7,89,"We would surely be fabricating a lie against God if we were to return to your faith after God has saved us from it. It does not befit us to return to it unless it is the Will of God, our Lord. Our Lord has encompassed everything in ˹His˺ knowledge. In God we trust. Our Lord! Judge between us and our people with truth. You are the best of those who judge.”"
  7,90,"The disbelieving chiefs of his people threatened, “If you follow Shu’aib, you will surely be losers!”"
  7,91,Then an ˹overwhelming˺ earthquake struck them and they fell lifeless in their homes
  7,92,Those who rejected Shu’aib were ˹wiped out˺ as if they had never lived there. Those who rejected Shu’aib were the true losers
  7,93,"He turned away from them, saying, “O my people! Indeed, I have delivered to you the messages of my Lord and gave you ˹sincere˺ advice. How can I then grieve for those who chose to disbelieve?”"